[{"sha":"d8ad1badc2dc8243908cdb10e965812a803eff0c","author":{"name":"Mehdi Amini","email":"808100943be7b7010123d78912f654820a5ee1c1@google.com"},"message":"Disable test on the RUN line instead of excluding it in the BUILD file.

It is rare that we need to exclude a test in the build file (it is useful if it
hangs). Lit tests can be marked XFAIL / UNSUPPORTED instead.

Unfortunately this test only fails in assert mode, so it can't be marked "XFAIL".

// UNSUPPORTED: {{.*}}

is the syntax for lit, but google internal equivalent does not parse this, so we're
mangling the RUN line for now.
